38","1495–Male":"1495–Overleden","1496–1603":"1496–1603","1501–1536":"1501–1536","–1562":"–1562","1435–Male":"1435–Overleden","1440–1483":"1440–1483","1495":"1495","1440":"1440","1483":"1483","1470":"1470","1536":"1536","1514":"1514","1435":"1435","1501":"1501","1465":"1465","about 1501":"circa 1501","1496":"1496","1562":"1562","1463":"1463","15 August 1514":"15 augustus 1514","1538":"1538","1603":"1603","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Northill, Bedfordshire, England":"Northill, Bedfordshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Bossall, Yorkshire, England":"Bossall, Yorkshire, England"},"en":{"1465–15 August 1514":"1465–15 August 1514","1463–Female":"1463–Deceased","1465–1514":"1465–1514","1470–1538":"1470–1538","1495–Male":"1495–Deceased","1496–1603":"1496–1603","1501–1536":"1501–1536","–1562":"–1562","1435–Male":"1435–Deceased","1440–1483":"1440–1483","1495":"1495","1440":"1440","1483":"1483","1470":"1470","1536":"1536","1514":"1514","1435":"1435","1501":"1501","1465":"1465","about 1501":"about 1501","1496":"1496","1562":"1562","1463":"1463","15 August 1514":"15 August 1514","1538":"1538","1603":"1603","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","Northill, Bedfordshire, England":"Northill, Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom","Bossall, Yorkshire, England":"Bossall, Yorkshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Redman","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: occupational name from Middle English <i>red</i> (Old English <i>hrēod</i>) ‘reed’ + <i>-man</i>, presumably for a thatcher or reed-cutter. Compare   Reeder  .","English: in southeastern England sometimes a topographic name perhaps for someone who lived by a clearing, from Middle English <i>rede</i> (Old English <i>rēod</i>, <i>rȳd</i>) ‘clearing’ + <i>man</i>.","English: habitational name from Redmain (Cumberland), from Old English <i>rēad</i> ‘red’ + an uncertain second element, perhaps a dialect form of <i>man</i> ‘cairn’."],"variants":[{"name":"Reeder","meanings":["English: occupational name for someone who used reeds as a roofing material (a thatcher), a derivative of Middle English <i>rede</i> ‘reed’ + <i>-er</i>. Compare   Reed   and   Redman  .","English: topographic name for someone who lived by a clearing, a derivative of Middle English <i>rede</i>, <i>ride</i>, <i>rude</i> ‘clearing’ (see   Reed  ) + <i>-er</i>, synonymous and interchangeable with <i>atte Rede</i>, <i>atte Rude</i> ‘at the clearing’. This type of name, composed of a topographic term + <i>-er</i>, is common in Kent, Surrey and Sussex, and it is also found in Essex.","Dutch and German: variant of   Reder   3."]},{"name":"Redhead","meanings":["English:","nickname for someone with red hair, from Middle English <i>red</i> ‘red’ + <i>he(ve)d</i> ‘head’. Compare   Redman  .","habitational name from an unidentified place in northern England called <i>Redhead</i>, probably meaning ‘red headland’."]},{"name":"Rodman","meanings":["English: occupational name for a thatcher or reed-cutter, from Southwest Middle English <i>rod(e)</i>, <i>rud(e)</i> (Old English <i>hrēod</i>) ‘reed’ + <i>-man</i>. Synonymous with   Redman   1.","English: topographic name for someone who lived at a clearing, from Middle English <i>rode</i> (Old English <i>rodu</i>) or Southwest Middle English <i>rude</i> (Old English <i>rȳde</i>) ‘clearing’ + <i>man</i>. See   Redman   2.","Americanized form of German <b>Rodmann</b>: variant of <b>Rodemann</b> (see   Rodeman  )."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas Redman was born in 1465, in Bossall, Yorkshire, England, his father, Brian Redman, was 30 and his mother, Alice Davall, was 25. He had at least 2 sons and 2 daughters with Anne Scrope. He died on 15 August 1514, in his hometown, at the age of 49."},"et":{"1465–15 August 1514":"1465–15. august 1514","1463–Female":"1463–Surnud","1465–1514":"1465–1514","1470–1538":"1470–1538","1495–Male":"1495–Surnud","1496–1603":"1496–1603","1501–1536":"1501–1536","–1562":"–1562","1435–Male":"1435–Surnud","1440–1483":"1440–1483","1495":"1495","1440":"1440","1483":"1483","1470":"1470","1536":"1536","1514":"1514","1435":"1435","1501":"1501","1465":"1465","about 1501":"umbes 1501","1496":"1496","1562":"1562","1463":"1463","15 August 1514":"15. august 1514","1538":"1538","1603":"1603","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Northill, Bedfordshire, England":"Northill, Bedfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bossall, Yorkshire, England":"Bossall, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"1465–15 August 1514":"1465–15. elokuuta 1514","1463–Female":"1463–Kuollut","1465–1514":"1465–1514","1470–1538":"1470–1538","1495–Male":"1495–Kuollut","1496–1603":"1496–1603","1501–1536":"1501–1536","–1562":"–1562","1435–Male":"1435–Kuollut","1440–1483":"1440–1483","1495":"1495","1440":"1440","1483":"1483","1470":"1470","1536":"1536","1514":"1514","1435":"1435","1501":"1501","1465":"1465","about 1501":"noin 1501","1496":"1496","1562":"1562","1463":"1463","15 August 1514":"15. elokuuta 1514","1538":"1538","1603":"1603","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Northill, Bedfordshire, England":"Northill, Bedfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Bossall, Yorkshire, England":"Bossall, Yorkshire, England"},"fr":{"1465–15 August 1514":"1465–15 août 1514","1463–Female":"1463–Décédée","1465–1514":"1465–1514","1470–1538":"1470–1538","1495–Male":"1495–Décédé","14